  "prompt": "How do I increase font size in Quora?",
  "response": "To increase the font size on Quora, you have a few options depending on the device you're using:\n\n### **On a Computer (Web Browser):**\n1. **Browser Zoom:**\n   - Press `Ctrl` + `+` (Windows) or `Cmd` + `+` (Mac) to zoom in and increase the overall size of the webpage, including the text.\n   - Alternatively, hold `Ctrl` (Windows) or `Cmd` (Mac) and scroll up with your mouse wheel.\n\n2. **Browser Settings:**\n   - Most browsers allow you to change the font size in the settings. For example:\n     - In **Google Chrome**, go to `Settings` > `Appearance` > `Font Size` and adjust it.\n     - In **Firefox**, go to `Settings` > `General` > `Language and Appearance` > `Fonts and Colors`.\n\n### **On Mobile (Quora App):**\nQuora\u2019s mobile app does not have a built-in option to change the font size directly. However, you can adjust the system-wide font size on your device:\n1. **For Android:**\n   - Go to `Settings` > `Display` > `Font Size` and adjust the slider.\n2. **For iOS:**\n   - Go to `Settings` > `Display & Brightness` > `Text Size` and adjust the slider.\n\n### **On Mobile (Web Browser):**\n1. **Pinch-to-Zoom:**\n   - Use two fingers to pinch outwards on the screen to zoom in and increase the text size.\n2. **Browser Settings:**\n   - Some mobile browsers allow you to adjust the font size in their settings.\n\nIf Quora adds a built-in font size adjustment feature in the future, it will likely be found in the app\u2019s settings or accessibility options. For now, these methods should help!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
